conductivity.property_description: Whether or not a redstone component can be powered through this block.

collision.property_description:
Whether the block has a solid collision that stops entities like players.

Fluids are listed with a separate value.

affects_movement_speed.property_description: Whether walking on/through this block affects the movement of players or certain other entities.

inflicts_damage.property_description:
Whether the block inflicts damage in any way.
Obtained manually

movable.property_description: Whether it can be pushed by a piston, or whether attempting to push it destroys the block.

sticky.property_description:
If the block can be pulled by a sticky piston or an adjacent slime/honey block.

Slime and honey are listed as 'partially' as they are not sticky when pulled by one another.

blast_resistance.property_description: Determines how likely this block is to break from exposure to an explosion

hardness.property_description: Determines how fast the block can be mined

instant_mineable.property_description:
Whether this block can be instant-mined when using at least:

-Efficiency V Diamond/Netherite (Yes)

-Efficiency V Gold (With Gold)

-Haste 2 with Diamond or greater (With Haste)

luminosity.property_description: How much light the block emits.

height_all.property_description:
The block's upwards-facing collision surfaces.

Includes internal collisions.

Defaults to pixel values, this can be converted in the settings.

height_external.property_description:
The block's upwards-facing collision surfaces.

Does not include internal collisions.

Defaults to pixel values, this can be converted in the settings.

width_all.property_description:
The block's side-facing collision surfaces.

Includes internal collisions.

Defaults to pixel values, this can be converted in the settings.

width_external.property_description:
The block's side-facing collision surfaces.

Does not include internal collisions.

Defaults to pixel values, this can be converted in the settings.

collision_bottom_all.property_description:
The block's downwards-facing collision surfaces.

Includes internal collisions.

Defaults to pixel values, this can be converted in the settings.

collision_bottom_external.property_description:
The block's downwards-facing collision surfaces.

Does not include internal collisions.

Defaults to pixel values, this can be converted in the settings.

full_cube.property_description: Whether the block has a normal cube shape and has a full block collision on all sides.

bottom_face_has_full_square.property_description: This is true if the bottom face is a full square.

top_face_has_full_square.property_description: This is true if the top face is a full square.

side_face_has_full_square.property_description: This is true if the side face is a full square.

bottom_face_has_small_square.property_description: This is true if the bottom face contains a square of length 2 at its center.

top_face_has_small_square.property_description: This is true if the top face contains a square of length 2 at its center.

side_face_has_small_square.property_description: This is true if the north face contains a square of length 2 at its center.

top_face_has_rim.property_description: This is true if the top face contains a 2 pixel wide ring going around its edge

bottom_face_has_collision.property_description: This is true if the bottom side has collision at the outer face (meaning it has a hard hitbox that aligns with the block grid).

top_face_has_collision.property_description: This is true if the top side has collision at the outer face (meaning it has a hard hitbox that aligns with the block grid).

side_face_has_collision.property_description: This is true if the north side has collision at the outer face (meaning it has a hard hitbox that aligns with the block grid).

obstructs_cactus.property_description: Whether placing this block next to cactus destroys it.

waterloggable.property_description: Whether this block can be waterlogged.

enderman_holdable.property_description: Whether endermen can pick up and hold this block.

dragon_immune.property_description: Whether this block is immune to The Ender Dragon flying through it.

wither_immune.property_description: Whether this block is immune to the skull projectiles shot by The Wither.

suffocates_mobs.property_description: Whether a mob or player should suffocate in this block.

spawnable.property_description: Whether mobs can spawn on this block.

flammable.property_description: Whether the block can be destroyed by/can sustain fire.

catches_fire_from_lava.property_description: Whether this block will catch fire from nearby lava.

send_comparator_updates.property_description: Whether interactions with this block sends updates to comparators up to 2 blocks away (manhattan distance).

survival_available.property_description:
Whether the block is avalible in normal survival gameplay.

Yes means the block is either obtainable as an item, or can easily be created anywhere in the world.

Uncreatable means the block cannot be created or obtained in conventional ways, but the block is still avalible in the world.

No means the block is exclusive to creative mode/cheats.

gets_flushed.property_description: Whether this block will get destroyed by flowing water.

instrument.property_description: Which instrument a noteblock will play if placed above this block.

gets_random_ticked.property_description: Whether the block gets affected by random ticks.

tile_entity_data.property_description: Whether the block is a tile entity, and if so, what the tile entity stores

Furnace:
-Time until the current item is smelted,
-The time until the furnace's current fuel item is exhausted,
-All of the items that have been smelted since a player emptied the output slot
Hopper: Time until the next transfer of an item
Smoker:
-Time until the current item is smelted,
-The time until the furnace's current fuel item is exhausted,
-All of the items that have been smelted since a player emptied the output slot
Blast Furnace:
-Time until the current item is smelted,
-The time until the furnace's current fuel item is exhausted,
-All of the items that have been smelted since a player emptied the output slot
Lectern: Page the book is currently on
entries.Beacon:
The pyramid level, active effects, and contents.
Also uses the block's position for the beacon beam
entries.Spawner:
-The entity to be spawned,
-The delay until the next entity is spawned, and the min and max values for the next spawn delay
-How many entities to spawn per spawn attempt
-Additional data about the entity to be spawned (such as position, status effects, and entities stacked on top of it)
Also uses the block's position to display the spinning mob inside

Piston.Moving piston:
-Offset of the block,
-Direction of movement,
-ID (and data value, if applicable) of the moving block

entries.Jukebox: Play music discs, if any are inside

Heads.Player Head: For the (if applicable) data of the player represented

entries.Command Blocks: Command text, its output strength, and the output text
entries.End Gateway: Teleport location and also whether to render the beam
entries.Jigsaw Block: The structure pool and the block this jigsaw block becomes
entries.Daylight Detector: To force the daylight sensor to update its output signal strength
entries.Conduit:
To check its activation area for valid activation blocks and calculate its effective range.
Also used for rendering the block in its active and inactive states
entries.Bell: For the render of the swaying animation of the bell

comparator_output.property_description:
What value a comparator will read from this block. Obtained from the wiki.
Chest- or Hopper Minecarts placed on detector rails will also give an output identical to their respective blocks.
Item frames can also give an output of 0 if there is no item inside, or a value from 1 to 8 depending on the item rotation.

map_color.property_description: The color of this block when viewed on a map. CLEAR is transparent, meaning it is simply ignored.

opaque.property_description: Whether the block is visually opaque. Used solely in rendering.

redirects_redstone.property_description: This is true if the North side connects to/redirects adjacent redstone dust
